-- At least 20 People Killed in Karachi After Pakistani Lawmaker Haider Shot
-- Farhan Sharif
-- 2010-08-03T03:25:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-03/at-least-20-people-killed-in-karachi-after-pakistani-lawmaker-haider-shot.html

          
          
             At least 20 people were killed in
protests in Karachi after Pakistani lawmaker Raza Haider was
killed last night, police information officer Mohammed Salim
said in a telephone interview from Karachi.  
 “It is an act of terrorism,” federal minister Muhammad
Farooq Sattar said in a telephone interview. “Haider was
targeted due to his work against terrorists.”  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
